90",{"author":546,"date":570,"citedRange":571,"ptr":572,"ref":574},"2012","189 n.28",{"target":573},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/CJISRIUV",{"_":575,"target":575},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001357",{"author":577,"date":578,"citedRange":579,"ptr":580,"ref":582},"Prag and Tigano","2017","no.38",{"target":581},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/MI64NB9L",{"_":583,"target":583},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630",{"type":585,"bibl":228},"discussion",[587],{"n":390,"url":115,"height":391,"width":392,"desc":116,"surfaceType":387},{"title":589,"body":590,"divs":591,"images":605},"ISic000584. Funerary inscription for Marcus Limbricius and his wife Helvia Arura","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000584_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina\" src=\"ISic000584_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000584.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina\" src=\"ISic000584-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>MLIMBRICIUSMF\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>FALRUFUS\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>VSIBIETHELVIAEARURAE\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>UXORISUAE\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Marcus Limbricius Rufus, son of Marcus, of the Falerna tribe (set this up) while alive for himself and for his wife Helvia Arura.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>As a funerary inscription, this text must originally have stood with a tomb outside the city, before being transported at a later date to the church where it was first recorded in the sixteenth century in a manuscript of Atonio Agust√≠n (Matritensis 5781 f.22 no.9, ap. Prestianni Giallombardo 1993a: Tav.1). The form of the letters suggests a text of the first century AD. Limbricius is probably of Campanian origin, and Puteoli specifically, as suggested by the other evidence for the family and tribe; Cicero attests to the interest of businessmen from Puteoli in Sicily (Verr. 2.5.154; see further Facella 2006: 210-211; the Falerna tribe is not otherwise attested in Sicily, see Prag 2010). The name Helvia is common, and Arura is one of a group of names linked to geographic origin and rural background.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 no. 142 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/310972\" target=\"_blank\">47 no. 301\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Muratori 1740 1366 no. 11 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001395\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001395\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1753 151-152 no. 9 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1769 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501431\" target=\"_blank\">cl. 11 no. 31\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501848\" target=\"_blank\">cl. 11 no. 32\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650803\" target=\"_blank\">10.7460\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Prestianni Giallombardo 1993 529 fig.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001659\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001659\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Facella 2006 210-211 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002013\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002013\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Scibona and Tigano 2008 52 ph \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001590\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001590\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Prestianni Giallombardo 2012 189 n.28 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001357\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001357\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Prag and Tigano 2017 no.38 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[592,594,596,598,600,602],{"id":400,"html":593},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>MLIMBRICIUSMF\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003C